text: Bronckhorst is a municipality in the province of Gelderland, the Netherlands. About 36,000 people were living there in 2021. Bronckhorst lies in the regions of Achterhoek and IJsselvallei. A small part in the southwest lies in the region of Liemers. It was created from the former municipalities of Hengelo, Hummelo en Keppel, Steenderen, Vorden, and Zelhem on 1 January 2005. == References == * Plaatsengids.nl Category:2005 establishments in the Netherlands Category:Municipalities of Gelderland Category:Achterhoek Category:IJsselvallei Category:Liemers
